Given the pressing need for a marked increase in #defense spending on national security grounds, markets fail to construe that the #Fed faces no choice but to accommodate the wartime #fiscal and defense policies of the Treasury and the DoD in promptly rebuilding the military industrial base within the sovereign borders of the US.  Against the backdrop of rather restrictive real rates and elevated risks of geopolitical tensions materialising across the globe, we advance firmly and deeper into a geo-economic regime of persistent #war premia not only in #gold but also in haven currencies. Tumaina imitative in Kenya will pave the way for a new political dispensation and a comprehensive peace agreement in South Sudan. This agreement aims to bring all none signatories to RARCSS together to form an inclusive political government, ensuring sustainable peace and stability.   It is crucial for all political forces to support this initiative, viewing it as a positive step towards overcoming current structural challenges. The proposed restructuring should include reducing overload in government executives and legislatures at all levels.  Key changes involve streamlining government roles, such as establishing the office of the Prime Minister and reducing ministries to 19 with 6 Deputies, 11 Independent Commissions and 4 parastatals.   The President remains the head of state and government with only one Vice President. The Prime Minister runs day to day function of the supervision of the cabinet in consultation with the president.   Additionally, restructuring the National Assembly and Council of States(270 and 52 members respectively) to enhance political representation and governance effectiveness.  Restructure the states and Administrative Areas to 47 members of the Assmebly, 11 cabinet members and 6 commissions.    Moreover, separating the national army and security sector from politics, alongside comprehensive leadership training for top commanders, highlights a commitment to professionalization and effectiveness in command.   Looking ahead, the focus is on economic recovery, accountability, and regulation in sectors like mining. The next government is poised to steer the country towards growth and progress, emphasizing accountability and sustainability.  President Salva Kiir should seize this pivotal moment to achieve a comprehensive peace to lead South Sudan towards prosperity through the rule of law, justice, and equality and deny the spoilers a chance of holding our country in conflict and destruction.  #supportTumainaInitiative.
